    • Method Detail

      • open

        void open(Properties connectionProperties)
        Send an event requesting that FIX connection according to the specified properties be opened.

        To open an accepting FIX connection specify the following property only:

        • LISTENPORT_PROPERTY

        To open an initiating FIX connection specify the following properties:

        • HOSTNAME_PROPERTY
        • PORT_PROPERTY
        • MAX_CONNECTION_ATTEMPTS (optional - if not specified behavior is implementation dependent)
        • CONNECTION_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS (optional - if not specified behavior is implementation dependent)
        Parameters:
        connectionProperties - Connection properties.

      • close

        void close(Properties connectionProperties)
        Send an event requesting that the FIX connection matching the specified properties be closed.

        It is up to the underlying implementation to decide what to do if the connection properties are not supplied, empty, or do not match any existing connection.

        Parameters:
        connectionProperties - The connection properties.
